        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 1:09PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 109 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Topaz Lake, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Smith, Wellington, Nv 208 At Douglas-Lyon Co Line, Smith Valley,
Artesia Lake, Holbrook Junction, and Mount Siegel.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
